My parents complain of mosquito bites every time to work in the garden close to the bamboo, so I suspect there should be some mosquito larvae somewhere. mosquitohabitatmapperComments: I haven’t seen any mosquitos moving around here, and it’s a man-made ditch my parents made to curb the growth of bamboo. Unfortunately, it fills up with water every time it rains. Although no mosquitos were present when observing, the shade and still water make it an ideal place for breeding. My parents complain of mosquito bites every time to work in the garden close to the bamboo, so I suspect there should be some mosquito larvae somewhere. I’ve taken a sample of the water and will wait to see if there are any larvae developments. There were some small insects on the surface of the water, although they looked more like small flies than mosquitos.
